      "type": "user-query",
      "text": "Research how Cursor IDE stores its AI coding sessions. I need to know:\n1. Where the session data is stored (file path, database location)\n2. What format it uses (SQLite, JSON, JSONL, etc.)\n3. The schema/structure of the session data\n4. What fields are available (messages, tool calls, file edits, timestamps)\n\nSearch the web for \"Cursor IDE session storage format\" and \"Cursor AI session data structure\". Also check if there's any documentation or open-source code that shows how to read Cursor sessions.\n\nReturn a detailed summary of the storage format, file paths, and schema.",
