    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "I now have comprehensive information. Here is a detailed summary of how Cursor IDE stores its AI coding sessions.\n\n---\n\n# Cursor IDE Session Storage: Complete Reference\n\n## 1. Storage Locations\n\nCursor stores all conversation data **locally** on disk, even when connected to a remote host via SSH. There are two distinct storage systems depending on which Cursor product you use:\n\n### A. Cursor Desktop App (Composer / Chat UI)\n\nAll data lives under the user's application support directory:\n\n| OS | Base Path |\n|---|---|\n| **macOS** | `~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/` |\n| **Windows** | `%APPDATA%\\Cursor\\User\\` (typically `C:\\Users\\<user>\\AppData\\Roaming\\Cursor\\User\\`) |\n| **Linux** | `~/.config/Cursor/User/` |\n\nWithin the base path, there are two key SQLite database files:\n\n```\nCursor/User/\n  globalStorage/\n    state.vscdb              <-- Global DB: ALL conversation content for ALL projects\n    state.vscdb-wal          <-- WAL journal (uncommitted recent writes)\n    state.vscdb-shm          <-- Shared memory file\n  workspaceStorage/\n    <workspace-id-1>/\n      workspace.json          <-- Maps workspace hash to project folder path\n      state.vscdb             <-- Workspace DB: composer list, selected tabs, UI state\n    <workspace-id-2>/\n      workspace.json\n      state.vscdb\n    ...\n```\n\nAdditionally, plain-text agent transcripts are written to:\n- `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized-project-path>/agent-transcripts/<composerId>.txt`\n\n### B. Cursor Agent CLI (terminal-based agent)\n\nThe Cursor Agent CLI (available on Linux) stores per-session databases:\n- `~/.config/cursor/chats/` or `~/.cursor/chats/`\n- Each session has its own `store.db` SQLite file inside a nested directory structure\n- Associated JSONL transcript files may also exist alongside\n\n---\n\n## 2. Storage Format: SQLite Key-Value Databases\n\n### Desktop App Format (`state.vscdb`)\n\nEvery `.vscdb` file is a **SQLite 3 database** running in **WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) mode**. Both the global and workspace databases share the same table schema:\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE ItemTable    (key TEXT UNIQUE, value BLOB);\nCREATE TABLE cursorDiskKV (key TEXT UNIQUE, value BLOB);\n```\n\nBoth tables are simple **key-value stores**. The `key` column holds a string identifier, and the `value` column holds a **BLOB that is typically a UTF-8 encoded JSON string**.\n\n**Important WAL note:** When reading while Cursor is open, you may need to copy all three files (`state.vscdb`, `state.vscdb-wal`, `state.vscdb-shm`) to get consistent data. Alternatively, open with `?mode=ro&immutable=1` to skip WAL recovery (you may miss the very latest writes).\n\n### Agent CLI Format (`store.db`)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE blobs (id TEXT PRIMARY KEY, data BLOB);\nCREATE TABLE meta (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, value TEXT);\n```\n\nThe `meta` table stores session metadata as **hex-encoded JSON** under key `\"0\"`. The `blobs` table uses content-addressed storage (SHA-256 hashes as IDs) with binary-encoded structures containing embedded JSON payloads.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Global DB Schema (`globalStorage/state.vscdb`) -- `cursorDiskKV` Key Patterns\n\nThis is where the actual conversation content lives for **all projects**. The key patterns in the `cursorDiskKV` table are:\n\n| Key Pattern | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `composerData:<composerId>` | **Session header/metadata** -- name, status, conversation index, modes, timestamps |\n| `bubbleId:<composerId>:<bubbleId>` | **Individual message bubbles** -- the source of truth for all message content (~60+ fields each) |\n| `checkpointId:<composerId>:<checkpointId>` | Workspace state snapshots (file diffs per agent turn) for the \"Restore\" feature |\n| `messageRequestContext:<composerId>:<messageId>` | Full request context sent to the model (file contents, git diffs, terminal output) |\n| `composer.content.<hash>` | Content-addressed blobs (large text shared across conversations, e.g., full file contents) |\n| `agentKv:*` | Background-agent KV state (message/blob archive with role, content, provider options) |\n| `codeBlockDiff:<composerId>:<diffId>` | Diff data for individual code blocks |\n| `codeBlockPartialInlineDiffFates:*` | Inline-diff acceptance state |\n| `ofsContent:*` | File-system content cache |\n\nThe `ItemTable` in the global DB holds:\n- `composer.composerHeaders` (Cursor 3.0+): Central index of all composers across all workspaces, tagged with `workspaceIdentifier`\n- Various UI state keys (`workbench.backgroundComposer.persistentData`, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Workspace DB Schema (`workspaceStorage/<hash>/state.vscdb`)\n\n### `ItemTable` -- Key: `composer.composerData`\n\nIn Cursor 2.x, this was the primary session index per workspace. In Cursor 3.0+, it was migrated to the global DB but still retains:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"allComposers\": [\n    {\n      \"composerId\": \"368a3d8e-...\",\n      \"type\": \"head\",\n      \"name\": \"Candidate assessment flow...\",\n      \"subtitle\": \"page.tsx, route.ts, ...\",\n      \"createdAt\": 1771860348535,\n      \"lastUpdatedAt\": 1771865761688,\n      \"unifiedMode\": \"agent\",\n      \"forceMode\": \"edit\",\n      \"createdOnBranch\": \"main\",\n      \"totalLinesAdded\": 1978,\n      \"totalLinesRemoved\": 139,\n      \"filesChangedCount\": 18,\n      \"contextUsagePercent\": 37.5,\n      \"hasUnreadMessages\": false,\n      \"isArchived\": false,\n      \"isDraft\": false,\n      \"isWorktree\": false,\n      \"isSpec\": false,\n      \"isBestOfNSubcomposer\": false,\n      \"numSubComposers\": 0,\n      \"referencedPlans\": []\n    }\n  ],\n  \"selectedComposerIds\": [\"...\"],\n  \"lastFocusedComposerIds\": [\"...\"],\n  \"hasMigratedComposerData\": true,\n  \"hasMigratedMultipleComposers\": true\n}\n```\n\n### `workspace.json`\n\nMaps the workspace directory hash to the actual project folder:\n```json\n{ \"folder\": \"file:///Users/you/Projects/my-app\" }\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Session Header Schema (`composerData:<composerId>`)\n\nEach entry in `cursorDiskKV` keyed by `composerData:<composerId>` is a JSON object:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"_v\": 13,\n  \"composerId\": \"fda95e1a-...\",\n  \"name\": \"Project structure and issues\",\n  \"createdAt\": 1737316260000,\n  \"lastUpdatedAt\": 1737316718874,\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"unifiedMode\": \"agent\",\n  \"forceMode\": \"edit\",\n  \"isAgentic\": true,\n\n  \"fullConversationHeadersOnly\": [\n    { \"bubbleId\": \"uuid-1\", \"type\": 1 },\n    { \"bubbleId\": \"uuid-2\", \"type\": 2, \"serverBubbleId\": \"...\" }\n  ],\n\n  \"conversationMap\": { },\n\n  \"context\": {\n    \"fileSelections\": [...],\n    \"folderSelections\": [...],\n    \"terminalSelections\": [...],\n    \"cursorRules\": [...],\n    \"selectedDocs\": [...]\n  },\n\n  \"latestConversationSummary\": {\n    \"summary\": \"...\",\n    \"truncationLastBubbleIdInclusive\": \"...\",\n    \"clientShouldStartSendingFromInclusiveBubbleId\": \"...\",\n    \"lastBubbleId\": \"...\"\n  },\n\n  \"codeBlockData\": {\n    \"file:///path/to/file.ts\": [\n      {\n        \"_v\": 2,\n        \"bubbleId\": \"...\",\n        \"codeBlockIdx\": 0,\n        \"uri\": { \"fsPath\": \"/path/to/file.ts\", \"scheme\": \"file\" },\n        \"version\": 0,\n        \"status\": \"accepted\",\n        \"languageId\": \"typescript\",\n        \"diffId\": \"...\",\n        \"isNoOp\": false\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n\n  \"usageData\": {\n    \"default\": {\n      \"costInCents\": 8,\n      \"amount\": 2\n    }\n  },\n\n  \"modelConfig\": { \"modelName\": \"composer-1\", \"maxMode\": false },\n\n  \"workspaceIdentifier\": {\n    \"id\": \"b9d81724966720d40c87d7f4e9983d73\",\n    \"uri\": { \"fsPath\": \"/Users/you/Projects/my-app\", \"scheme\": \"file\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nKey fields:\n- `fullConversationHeadersOnly[]` -- ordered list of message references (bubbleId + type). This is the conversation ordering index.\n- `type` values: `1` = user message, `2` = assistant message\n- `conversationMap` -- legacy message content cache (empty in v3 storage)\n- `context` -- attached files, folders, terminal selections, cursor rules, docs\n- `codeBlockData` -- grouped by file path; each entry tracks code suggestion status (accepted/rejected/completed)\n- `usageData` -- token/cost usage summary per composer\n\n---\n\n## 6. Individual Message Bubble Schema (`bubbleId:<composerId>:<bubbleId>`)\n\nEach message is stored as its own key-value entry with approximately **70+ fields**. The reliable/core fields are:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"_v\": 3,\n  \"type\": 2,\n  \"bubbleId\": \"7dd300cc-6205-47ab-913e-fc921e68cef9\",\n  \"requestId\": \"uuid-of-server-request\",\n  \"usageUuid\": \"billing-uuid\",\n\n  \"text\": \"The actual message text...\",\n\n  \"tokenCount\": {\n    \"inputTokens\": 412,\n    \"outputTokens\": 188\n  },\n\n  \"modelInfo\": { \"modelName\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5\" },\n\n  \"createdAt\": 1731539400000,\n\n  \"workspaceUris\": [\"file:///path/to/project\"],\n\n  \"thinking\": { \"text\": \"Chain of thought reasoning...\" },\n  \"allThinkingBlocks\": [...],\n  \"thinkingDurationMs\": 1234,\n\n  \"toolResults\": [...],\n  \"mcpDescriptors\": [...],\n  \"supportedTools\": [...],\n\n  \"capabilityType\": \"...\",\n  \"capabilities\": [...],\n  \"capabilityContexts\": [...],\n  \"capabilityStatuses\": [...],\n\n  \"codeBlocks\": [{ \"language\": \"rust\" }, { \"language\": \"ts\" }],\n  \"suggestedCodeBlocks\": [...],\n\n  \"editTrailContexts\": [...],\n  \"fileDiffTrajectories\": [...],\n  \"gitDiffs\": [...],\n  \"humanChanges\": [...],\n  \"diffsSinceLastApply\": [...],\n  \"assistantSuggestedDiffs\": [...],\n\n  \"toolFormerData\": {\n    \"name\": \"read_file\",\n    \"params\": \"{\\\"targetFile\\\": \\\"/path/to/file\\\"}\",\n    \"result\": \"{\\\"contents\\\": \\\"...\\\"}\",\n    \"status\": \"completed\",\n    \"additionalData\": { \"status\": \"completed\" }\n  },\n\n  \"richText\": { ... },\n  \"context\": { ... },\n  \"checkpointId\": \"...\"\n}\n```\n\nField details:\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `_v` | number | Schema version (currently `3` in 99.8% of rows) |\n| `type` | number | `1` = user message, `2` = assistant message |\n| `text` | string | Message text (may be empty for tool-call or thinking bubbles) |\n| `bubbleId` | uuid | Within-session message ID |\n| `requestId` | uuid | Server request ID, shared across bubbles in the same turn |\n| `tokenCount` | object | `{ inputTokens, outputTokens }` -- **unreliable: 96% report {0,0}** |\n| `createdAt` | number (ms) | Timestamp (may be absent on some user messages) |\n| `richText` | object | Structured representation of user input |\n| `thinking` / `allThinkingBlocks` | various | Extended thinking / chain-of-thought output |\n| `thinkingDurationMs` | number | Duration of thinking in milliseconds |\n| `toolResults` | array | Results from tool calls (file edits, terminal commands, etc.) |\n| `codeBlocks` | array | Code blocks in assistant responses |\n| `suggestedCodeBlocks` | array | Diffs the assistant proposed |\n| `toolFormerData` | object | Tool call metadata: name, params, result, status |\n| `mcpDescriptors` / `supportedTools` | various | MCP (Model Context Protocol) tool descriptors |\n| `capabilityType` / `capabilities` | various | Agent capability invocations |\n| `editTrailContexts` / `fileDiffTrajectories` / `gitDiffs` | various | File-edit tracking data |\n| `checkpointId` | uuid | Reference to workspace checkpoint (on user messages in agent mode) |\n| `workspaceUris` | string[] | `file://...` URIs (**sparse -- only 11% of sessions**) |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Checkpoint Data (`checkpointId:<composerId>:<checkpointId>`)\n\nWorkspace state snapshots taken before each agent turn:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"uri\": { \"path\": \"/path/to/file.py\", \"scheme\": \"vscode-remote\" },\n      \"originalModelDiffWrtV0\": [\n        {\n          \"original\": { \"startLineNumber\": 10, \"endLineNumberExclusive\": 15 },\n          \"modified\": [\"new line 1\", \"new line 2\"]\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"nonExistentFiles\": [],\n  \"newlyCreatedFolders\": [],\n  \"activeInlineDiffs\": [],\n  \"inlineDiffNewlyCreatedResources\": []\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Cursor Agent CLI Schema (`store.db`)\n\nA separate storage system for the Cursor Agent CLI:\n\n### Meta Table\n```json\n{\n  \"agentId\": \"...\",\n  \"latestRootBlobId\": \"...\",\n  \"name\": \"session name\",\n  \"mode\": \"...\",\n  \"createdAt\": 1737316260000,\n  \"lastUsedModel\": \"...\"\n}\n```\n\n### Blobs Table\nContent-addressed (SHA-256) binary blobs containing message objects:\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"...\",\n  \"role\": \"user\" | \"assistant\",\n  \"content\": [\n    { \"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"...\" },\n    { \"type\": \"tool_use\", \"toolName\": \"Bash\", \"args\": {...} },\n    { \"type\": \"tool_result\", \"toolCallId\": \"...\", \"result\": \"...\" }\n  ],\n  \"providerOptions\": { \"cursor\": { \"requestId\": \"...\" } }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. Tools for Reading Cursor Sessions\n\nSeveral open-source projects can extract and export Cursor sessions:\n\n| Project | Language | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| [**cursaves**](https://github.com/Callum-Ward/cursaves) | Python | Full backup/migration tool for Cursor sessions; handles both v2.x and v3.0+ schemas |\n| [**cursor-session**](https://github.com/iksnae/cursor-session) | Go | CLI to list, show, and export sessions in JSONL, Markdown, YAML, JSON |\n| [**cursor-history**](https://github.com/S2thend/cursor-history) | TypeScript/Node.js | JS API and CLI for session management with full conversation export |\n| [**chat-grabber** (convoptics)](https://github.com/brenoneill/convoptics) | -- | Detailed schema documentation and Cursor adapter |\n| [**copilot-lens**](https://github.com/pavanvamsi3/copilot-lens) | TypeScript | Multi-platform session viewer with Cursor support |\n| [**cursor-efficiency**](https://github.com/pppp606/cursor-efficiency) | -- | Schema documentation for v0.50.5 |\n| [**atrium-adapters**](https://github.com/jonnyasmar/atrium-adapters) | Python | Cursor Agent CLI session extractor |\n| [**sidecar**](https://github.com/marcus/sidecar) | Go | Cursor CLI adapter reading store.db blobs |\n\n### Reading the Database (quick example in Node.js)\n\n```javascript\n// Using node:sqlite (Node 22.5+)\nimport { DatabaseSync } from 'node:sqlite';\n\nconst db = new DatabaseSync(\n  'file:/path/to/globalStorage/state.vscdb?mode=ro&immutable=1',\n  { readOnly: true }\n);\n\n// List all sessions\nconst composers = db.prepare(\n  \"SELECT key, value FROM cursorDiskKV WHERE key LIKE 'composerData:%'\"\n).all();\n\n// Get messages for a session\nconst bubbles = db.prepare(\n  \"SELECT key, value FROM cursorDiskKV WHERE key LIKE 'bubbleId:<composerId>:%'\"\n).all();\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. Key Caveats and Fragility\n\n1. **Schema version `_v`:** The bubble schema version is currently `3`. Values other than `3` should be handled defensively.\n2. **`tokenCount` is unreliable:** 96% of assistant bubbles report `{0,0}` for input/output tokens.\n3. **`workspaceUris` is sparse:** Only 11% of sessions populate this. Use the workspace registry (`workspace.json` + `workspaceIdentifier`) instead.\n4. **`conversationMap` is legacy:** In v3 storage, this field is empty or absent; messages are in individual `bubbleId:` entries.\n5. **Cursor 3.0 migration (April 2026):** The per-workspace `allComposers` array was centralized into `composer.composerHeaders` in the global DB. Old sessions not re-opened since migration may not appear in the central index.\n6. **Sub-composers / best-of-N:** Sessions with `numSubComposers > 0` represent parallel exploration branches; each is a separate composer row.\n7. **No encryption:** Data is stored as plain JSON in SQLite -- there is no encryption or obfuscation.\n8. **WAL locking:** The database may have a non-trivial WAL file. Copy all three files (`.vscdb`, `-wal`, `-shm`) for consistent reads, or use `immutable=1` mode.",
      "timestamp": 1783287728368
